<h4 id="steps-">Steps :</h4>

<h5 id="hardware-">Hardware :</h5>

<p><img src="/images/Screenshot 2022-09-02 at 10.37.36.png" alt="" />
<strong>Servo and titl sensor</strong></p>

<p>** Place the <strong>tilt sensor</strong> on the breadboard, connect the pins, one to the - on the board, keep middle empty, the last to the arduino, one of the digital pins. To know which is ground and which is power, refer back to the manual.</p>

<p>** Then add a resistor with 10 kÎ© connecting from the + side of the tilt sensor</p>

<ul>
  <li>Tilt sensor with passive buzzers + adding different tones</li>
  <li>Using the magic cup tilt sensor for lights</li>
</ul>

